00:07:09.180 --> 00:07:11.120
Osmoregulation in humans.

00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:16.980
The kidney is the main organ responsible for osmoregulation in humans.

00:07:17.760 --> 00:07:23.980
Water, amino acids, and glucose are reabsorbed by the kidneys.

00:07:24.940 --> 00:07:31.800
When the water level in the body is high, it releases a large amount of hypotonic urine.

00:07:32.240 --> 00:07:40.020
When the water is low, it retains water and produces a low amount of hypotonic urine.

00:07:40.760 --> 00:07:46.040
Thus, the kidney maintains the electrolytic balance of the body.

00:07:46.940 --> 00:07:53.420
The kidneys are two bean-shaped organs, each about the size of a fist.

00:07:53.420 --> 00:07:59.400
They are located just below the rib cage, one on each side of your spine.

00:08:00.680 --> 00:08:07.680
However, the kidney filters about a half cup of blood every minute, removing waste and

00:08:07.680 --> 00:08:10.280
extra water to make urine.

